7 TIPS TO KEEP YOU MOTIVATED 💪🏽

Here are my top 7 tips to help you stay on track
1. Do exercise you enjoy and find exciting - doing exercise you like and have excitement for will have you looking forwards to all your workouts. 
2. Learn a new skill - learning new skills always makes you want to come back and try it again and improve. 
3. Schedule in your workouts to your diary - just like your work set your workouts in your diary so it’s set in. 
4. Set small achievable goals - small goals will lead to your big goal and will keep it challenging
5. Find a workout partner - finding someone who’s like you to train with will help you stay motivated and push eachother on. 
6. Remember why your exercising - times when you feel like your unmotivated remember why your training and what you want to achieve. 
7. Find beautiful locations to train - training in beautiful locations just makes your workouts all worth it 💪🏽
Tag and share with a friend who needs this. ❤️

Good luck and Dm me for any questions. 

Be The Fittest 💪🏽💪🏽💪🏽

This was the CRAZIEST boat trip ever! These waves 🌊 were relentless I know on vid it doesn’t look that bad trust me they were. I have never had to go into the deepest form of meditation in my LIFE. 😂 So we were on our way to a challenge and got on this boat which was like a 2 hour ride, at the beginning we all had banter, messing and joking around then the waves started real quick and I remember thinking 5 min in, I’m not feeling good and the waves leaving my stomach in the air, up and down, up and down, I started getting real anxious knowing there was 2 hours of this and being trapped on this boat there was NO WHERE TO GO LOL. The jokes and bants stopped real quick lol. I remember at that point I had to go into the deepest form of meditation and somehow find relaxation, my mind had to focus on being one with the waves, breathe and not have a full blown panic attack lol I was like full mode zen 100. I remember thinking just Look into the horizon, look at the beautiful world, this is life🙏🏽
Shortly after everyone started feeling it too, people getting sick, then passing out, someone fighting the air lol. What’s crazy is that when people were passing out, all the anxiety in my mind went away and my focus became on them. Literally didn’t know what was going on but it came like final destination movie hahaha! Was the craziest struggle to get to this island but once we made it to the island we all recovered and got back 100%. This was a journey we will never forget! Forget Alton towers just get on a wild boat lol 

New episodes of GO HARD OR GO HOME this Sunday on @bbc @bbc @bbc it’s going to be a big one!

Crazy Yoga story: It’s funny how things in life come full circle. When I was about age 21/22 during a time in my life when things were not going well at all for me and there seemed to be no hope for me or my future. Things were at a deep low. I remember my cousin came to me and brought me this book on yoga saying i needed it in my life and all I remember was me thinking, okay I want to try it but did not understand one word in this book, like what was a “vinyasa” or what on earth is an “asana” lol. So I decided to just look at the pictures and try a few of the moves and I did it for a few days but then just ended up putting this book down. Years later I decided to try change my life around, I started my business and I ended up some how getting into yoga and I remember trying to research and learn from teachers on YouTube. I came across this teacher on YouTube and something really resonated with me, I loved the style of his teaching his enthusiasm, authenticity and he had a sick practice and I tried to learn as much as I could from his YouTube vids and remember thinking one day I’d actually love to learn from him. Anyway i remember thinking I had this book on yoga from years back so I went on a mission to try and find it, and when I eventually found the book I was shocked….this same book that I had from all those years back before I even got into yoga was written by the same person who i resonated with from these yoga YouTube videos that I came across and wanted to learn from! Was the same person! @johnscottyoga 🙈🙈 I remember thinking at that point this has come full circle, it’s meant to be 🙏🏽

#yogastory #story #fullcircle #crazystory #howigotintoyoga #yogi #fitnessyogi #tattedyogi #tatts #bookstagram
